President Donald J. Trump has nominated R. Alexander Acosta for the position of Secretary of Labor. Acosta is currently the Dean of Florida International University Law School and has had a long and distinguished career in public service. He has served in three Presidentially appointed, Senate-confirmed positions, including as a member of the National Labor Relations Board. Acosta was also the first Hispanic to hold the rank of Assistant Attorney General and served as the United States Attorney for the Southern District of Florida. Since 2013, Acosta has been the Chairman of U.S. Century Bank. President Trump believes that Acosta's extensive experience and passion for equal opportunity make him a highly qualified leader to support the American worker. Acosta is eager to serve his country and work tirelessly on behalf of the American worker.